public void clear()
        Deprecated. You should never call this function unless you known exactly what you are doing.
        This method is designed to clear a resource, use it at your own risks.

        The newly unsaved instance is kept in a reference, use backup() if you want to try to retrieve it afterwards.

      • backup

        @Deprecated
public T backup()
        Deprecated. You should never call this function unless you known exactly what you are doing.
        This method is designed to get back a cleared instance by clear().

        The lost instance is kept in a reference, there is absolutely NO guaranty that the instance would be available.

        Returns:
        the restored instance if any.
